The paper deals with the problem of accurately estimating the progress of SQL queries in decision support administration, which is a core problem in database management systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Database). The paper proposes a novel estimator selection framework that uses a statistical model, which involves machine learning techniques, to improve the robustness of progress estimation. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of selecting the best estimator for a given query based on its characteristics, which involves optimization techniques and decision-making algorithms, suggesting that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
